  "text": "Asus Vivobook 14 $320 $600 Save $280 You can go wrong if you're looking to buy a budget laptop with lots of power. Grab the Vivobook 14 with an Intel Core i5 and 12GB RAM for just $320 while this deal lasts. We've seen some impressive deals from Asus, knocking its Vivobook 14 line down to just $220. But if you are looking for something with a little more power and storage, we think this one with an Intel Core i5 and 12GB RAM is going to be right up your alley. Plus, you get a sleek design, and it's now not all that expensive thanks to a steep $280 discount that drops it down to just $320 for a very limited time. Related Best laptops in 2025 Looking for a new laptop for work, school, or anything else? Here are the very best laptops on the market right now. What's great about the Asus Vivobook 14? Source: Asus Sometimes you just need a laptop that's going to work and not cost a lot of money. Despite its low price, the Asus Vivobook 14 really manages to deliver when it comes to the overall experience. You get a nice 14-inch 1080p screen and plenty of power thanks to the Intel Core i5 processor. Furthermore, the laptop also packs 12GB of RAM and 256GB of SSD storage. It's thin, relatively light, and also has plenty of connectivity as well, with three USB-A, USB-C, HDMI, and a 3.5mm audio jack. The device also packs Wi-Fi 5 and Bluetooth 5.1 as well. Battery life is quoted at eight hours, and there's even a 720p web cam if you need to take or make video calls. It even has a unique trackpad that can transform into a number pad if needed. Overall, you're looking at something that can easily get through most things you throw at it, and it doesn't cost a lot of money. Not only is this laptop perfect for beginners and students, but it's also a good one to get if you're looking to do some light work, or just use it to browse the web and watch some movies. Just be sure to act quickly as the discount won't be around for long.",
