d a laptop that\u0026#39;s going to work and not cost a lot of money. Despite its low price, the Asus Vivobook 14 really manages to deliver when it comes to the overall experience. You get a nice 14-inch 1080p screen and plenty of power thanks to the Intel Core i5 processor. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eFurthermore, the laptop also packs 12GB of RAM and 256GB of SSD storage. It\u0026#39;s thin, relatively light, and also has plenty of connectivity as well, with three USB-A, USB-C, HDMI, and a 3.5mm audio jack. The device also packs Wi-Fi 5 and Bluetooth 5.1 as well. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eBattery life is quoted at eight hours, and there\u0026#39;s even a 720p web cam if you need to take or make video calls. It even has a unique trackpad that can transform into a number pad if needed. Overall, you\u0026#39;re looking at something that can easily get through most things you throw at it, and it doesn\u0026#39;t cost a lot of money.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eNot only is this laptop perfect for beginners and students, but it\u0026#39;s also a good one to get if you\u0026#39;re looking to do some light work, or just use it to browse the web and watch some movies. Just be sure to act quickly as the discount won\u0026#39;t be around for long. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
